name: Bluebird of Happiness Pendant Necklace
description: I created this stunning bluebird pendant by creating a frame out of wire, hammering the frame and then wrapping wire around that frame. I then wire wrapped these gorgeous blue pearls to it, and some 3mm and 4mm faceted tanzanite rondelles. I used black onyx rounds for the beak and for the eye. (By the way, happiness was what I was feeling when I finally finished this, it was kicking my butt for almost a week).

name: Turquoise Drop Earrings
description: These simply lovely earrings are in a new line of simple gorgeous earrings, perfect for any occasion-that I'm going to be listing. Simply wrapped 10mm round stabilized turquoise beads hung from sturdy sterling wires. Aren't they lovely?

name: Handmade Amethyst Wire Wrapped Earrings
description:
Who doesn't love purple? I took sterling wire and wrapped these absolutely amazing 12mm multi faceted coin amethyst beads. I then added some sterling diamond dust and 4mm amethyst bead dangles to the bottom. I really don't want to give these up...
Earrings measure about 1.5 inches long from the bottom of the earwires.
